{"title_page": "1963 1. divisjon", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Eliteserien|1. divisjon]]\n| season             = 1963\n| winners            = [[SK Brann|Brann]]<br />2nd title\n| relegated          = [[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]]<br/>[[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]]\n| continentalcup1    = [[1963\u201364 European Cup|European Cup]]           \n| continentalcup1 qualifiers = [[FK Lyn|Lyn]]\n| continentalcup2    = [[1964\u201365 European Cup Winners' Cup|Cup Winners' Cup]]\n| continentalcup2 qualifiers = [[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]]\n| continentalcup3    = [[1964\u201365 Inter-Cities Fairs Cup|Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]]\n| continentalcup3 qualifiers = [[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerengen]]\n| matches            = 90\n| total goals        = 336\n| league topscorer   = Leif Eriksen<br/>(16 goals)\n| biggest home win   = {{no break|Brann 8\u20131 [[Frigg Oslo FK|Frigg]]}}<br><small>(4 May 1963)\n| biggest away win   = {{no break|Frigg 0\u20137 V\u00e5lerengen}}<br><small>(19 May 1963)</small>\n| highest scoring    = {{no break|Brann 8\u20131 Frigg}}<br><small>(4 May 1963)\n| longest wins       = Brann<br/>Lyn<br/>Skeid<br/>(4 games)\n| longest unbeaten   = Lyn<br/>(10 games)\n| longest winless    = Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn<br/>(10 games)\n| longest losses     = Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn<br/>(6 games)\n| highest attendance = 20,897<br/>{{nobreak|Brann 1\u20131 [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]}}<br/><small>(19 May 1963)</small>\n| lowest attendance  = 2,375<br/>{{nobreak|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn 2\u20131 [[Sarpsborg FK]]}}<br/><small>(13 October 1963)</small>\n| average attendance = 7,871\n| prevseason         = [[1961\u201362 Norwegian Main League|Hovedserien 1961\u201362]]\n| nextseason         = [[1964 1. divisjon|1964]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1963 [[Eliteserien|1. divisjon]]''' was the 18th completed season of top division [[association football|football]] in [[Norway]]. This was the first regular season were all the top flight teams played in the same group.\n\n==Overview==\nIt was performed in 10 teams, and [[SK Brann|Brann]] won their second consecutive championship title.\n\n[[FK Lyn|Lyn]] lead the table after 9 games, and qualified for the [[1963\u201364 European Cup]]. \n\n[[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]] and [[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]] finished 9th and 10th and were relegated to the [[1. divisjon|2. divisjon]].\n\n==Teams and locations==\n:''Note: Table lists in alphabetical order.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Team\n!{{Tooltip| Ap. | Appearances in top divisions of Norwegian football}}\n! Location\n|-\n| [[SK Brann|Brann]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''14'''\n| [[Bergen]]\n|-\n| [[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''18'''\n| [[Fredrikstad]]\n|-\n| [[Frigg Oslo FK|Frigg]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''8'''\n| [[Oslo]]\n|-\n| [[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''4'''\n| [[Gj\u00f8vik]]\n|-\n| [[Lyn Fotball|Lyn]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''11'''\n| [[Oslo]]\n|-\n| [[Sarpsborg FK]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''13'''\n| [[Sarpsborg]]\n|-\n| [[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''17'''\n| [[Oslo]]\n|-\n| [[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''6'''\n| [[Steinkjer]]\n|-\n| [[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerengen]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''14'''\n| [[Oslo]]\n|-\n| [[Viking FK|Viking]]\n| align=\"center\"| '''18'''\n| [[Stavanger]]\n|}\n\n==League table==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=QR\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=SKB|name_SKB=[[SK Brann|Brann]]\n|team2=LYN|name_LYN=[[Lyn Fotball|Lyn]]\n|team3=SKD|name_SKD=[[Skeid Fotball|Skeid]]\n|team4=FFK|name_FFK=[[Fredrikstad FK|Fredrikstad]]\n|team5=FRI|name_FRI=[[Frigg Oslo FK|Frigg]]\n|team6=SAR|name_SAR=[[Sarpsborg FK]]\n|team7=VIK|name_VIK=[[Viking FK|Viking]]\n|team8=VIF|name_VIF=[[V\u00e5lerenga Fotball|V\u00e5lerengen]]\n|team9=SFK|name_SFK=[[Steinkjer FK|Steinkjer]]\n|team10=GJ\u00d8|name_GJ\u00d8=[[SK Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn|Gj\u00f8vik-Lyn]]\n\n|win_SKB=10|draw_SKB=4|loss_SKB=4|gf_SKB=46|ga